A lecturer with the Federal Polytechnic, Kaura Namoda, Zamfara State, Dr. Rabiu Adamu, has said that entrepreneurship plays a vital role in the economic development of the expanding Nigerian and global marketplace. Dr. Rabiu Adamu, Qurbin Maikia, who lectures at the Department of Business Administration and Management of the polytechnic, who addressed a press conference in Abuja, said come January 8, 2019, launch a two-volume compendium of the entrepreneurship spirit of Atiku Abubakar, the PDP presidential candidate. The two books, Entrepreneurship Development and Entrepreneurship Education, he said, were his thesis while studying in Uganda and said entrepreneurship is a multi-dimensional concept that covers every aspect of human life and cuts across various disciplines and called on tertiary and vocational institutions in Nigeria to include the subject in their schools. Dr. Adamu said entrepreneurship could be described as the capacity and willingness to develop, organize and manage a business venture along with any of its risks in order to make a profit by taking several risks in the corporate world or simply put, entrepreneurship is the willingness to start a new business. NBTE accuses FG of bias in  funding varsities, polytechnics 25th Anniversary: Minister lauds Fed Poly, Offa ‘Entrepreneurship, magic wand for nation’s development’